{
  "texts": [
    "Gibbs posteriors are discussed in a decision theoretic framework by Bissiri et al. (2016).",
    "An asymptotic study of Gibbs posteriors, using different arguments than PAC-Bayes bounds (but related), is provided by Syring and Martin (2023) and some the references therein.",
    "Finally, Bhattacharya et al. (2019, Theorem 3.4) proved a PAC-Bayes bound for tempered posteriors.",
    "A very active field of research is the study of the contraction of the posterior in Bayesian statistics: the objective is to prove that π(dθ|X 1,.",
    ", X n) concentrates around the true parameter θ * when n → ∞."
  ]
}